@{fg background}@{bg text} Introduction @{fg text}@{bg background}

The @{" Electrics ARexx Shell " LINK Picture_Database/AShell.0/MAIN} program is a command-line interface,
similar to the AmigaDOS command shell.  Any ARexx command may be run
from the ARexx Shell, with their results or messages displayed in the
window.  As in the AmigaDOS command shell, the UP and DOWN cursor keys
recall the command history.

The Amiga's RexxMast program must be running before an ARexx Shell
program can be run.

@{fg background}@{bg text} Shell Commands @{fg text}@{bg background}

There are a small number of commands that are used to control the
ARexx Shell program itself.

HELP
  
  Displays list of commands for controlling the Arexx Shell.

QUIT 
  
  Exits from the Shell program.
